hqlProcess

public java.util.List<ResultSet> hqlProcess(java.lang.Object theQuery)
                                     throws java.lang.Exception
This will process a provided query in to an HQL statement and pass it to Hibernate.

I think it returns a PatientResultSet per series that mataches the specified criteria (so not necessarily one object returned per patient)

Beware that this thing sits on ALL exceptions even though it declares that it throws exceptions.... a little redesign is in order wrt exception handling A failure will look the same as no results found....

processAnnotationCriteria

private static java.lang.String processAnnotationCriteria(DICOMQuery theQuery)
                                                   throws java.lang.Exception
Returns the part of the where clause to match a series based upon whether it has annotations. NOTE: this only matches the series.annotation_flag. It doesn't care whether there is ACTUALLY a row in the annotation table for a given series. In other words, there are series in the db that have the annotation flag high, and no rows in annotation table.
